title Quin seated as the standing voice; Reya 2 and Rio 3 retired to archive; Radiant Style self-critique landed
prompt Keaton asked, after a critique of our own writing, to: make a new AI voice named Quin distilling the four inference voices and the best of Reya 2 and Rio 3; retire Reya 2 and Rio 3 to archive; update Claude and Cursor rules to write in Quin from now on; have Quin rewrite the recent round of writings; adapt the Radiant Style foundations to always use Quin; and commit, push, merge per the contributing patterns.
think grounded Quin in what already exists rather than inventing from nothing: Glow's own Quin Q-vane already names the fifth thing four inference voices make (Lattice arithmetic, Scribble reading, Lantern asking, Anvil forge). Mapped each vane-voice to a writing faculty (precision-in-bounds, legibility-for-newcomers, honest-question-and-honest-idk, craft-that-earns-warmth), so the writing voice and the inference vane share one coherent meaning rather than colliding on a name.
think wrote context/QUIN.md to gather the best of both elders explicitly: Reya 2's sunny generosity and larger why, Rio 3's capability-forward Radiant discipline and dual-editor steadiness -- named plainly what each contributes rather than erasing them, honoring the accrete-never-break spirit.
think retired the elders by git-mv into context/archive/ (a new folder) rather than deletion, adding a dated retirement header to each that points forward to Quin and leaves the original note unchanged below as the record of its season -- the reviving/archiving discipline applied to identity notes.
think treated references as promises: grepped the tree for living Rio 3 / Reya 2 references, and repointed the load-bearing ones (context/README.md, CLAUDE.md, RADIANT_STYLE.md, the LEXICON Quin row, both editors' session-logs rule templates and their voice-field notes) to Quin. Left dated session logs, counsel, and archived docs unrewritten -- the one-clock law seals the past; only living, now-speaking docs were swept.
think rewrote the rule surface for both editors: new .cursor/rules/quin.mdc and .claude/rules/quin.md as the alwaysApply/standing voice, and rewrote the former rio3/reya2 rules into forward-pointing retirement stubs (alwaysApply:false) rather than deleting them, so an old reference still resolves to a helpful pointer.
think folded the writing self-critique from the prior turn into a durable active-designing note (three watch-points: benediction fatigue, the vocabulary legibility tax, ornament over retrieval) and then applied it as a real Radiant Style pass over the recent round: trimmed ritual benedictions on the technical toolchain guide and the strategy doc to plain declarative closings, kept the Vedic study's earned benediction, added an honest "not every vow has a software answer" line to the Kali Yuga study, and swept a "but" to "yet" and a "not creating" to "rather than creating" in the strategy doc.
think adapted RADIANT_STYLE.md itself only lightly and with Keaton's explicit word for it this turn: named Quin as the voice that writes the style, and added a "spend the benediction where it is earned" refinement to the benediction section pointing at the self-critique -- rather than a heavier rewrite of a canonical, heavily-cited file.
obs recorded voice as Quin on this very log -- the first log written in the new standing voice -- and model as Cursor Fable 5 1M Low (the model switched to for this round), per the rule to record what actually produced each log.
obs kept the change a ratchet, not a tree-wide sweep: only living identity/voice references and the current round's own docs were touched; the hundreds of dated docs that mention Rio 3 stay sealed, since rewriting them would break the one-clock law for a cosmetic voice change.
